-- Taiwan Stocks: Inotera Memories, Nanya Tech, Neo-Solar Power
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-02-04T05:50:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-04/taiwan-stocks-inotera-memories-nanya-tech-neo-solar-power.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 0.9 percent to 7,741.24, the eighth
day of gains and the longest winning streak since September
2009.  Inotera Memories Inc. (3474)  (3474 TT), a venture between  Nanya
Technology Corp. (2408)  and Micron Technology Inc., gained 4.3 percent
to NT$6.29. Inotera President Charles Kau said by phone today
that the death of Micron Chief Executive Officer Steve Appleton
would have no impact on its operations.  Nanya Technology Corp. (2408 TT) surged 6.6 percent to
NT$2.89, the highest close since Nov. 9. January sales climbed
28 percent from a month ago, according to statements to the
Taiwan Stock Exchange.  Neo-Solar Power Corp. (3576)  (3576 TT) slumped 6.9 percent to
NT$27.85, the biggest drop since Nov. 23. January revenue fell
65 percent to NT$850 million, the company said in a statement to
the Taiwan Stock Exchange yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
